ABOUT SHAMROCKIN' FEST
Sample BBQ, Chili & more
Shamrockin BBQ & Beer Festival is a festival created by the Firefighter Charity of Central Florida as a fundraiser for their Florian Fund. This fund helps local firefighters in time of a major personal crisis. The 2 day festival is a family fun event full of tastings, music, competitions, and more! We are passionate about creating an unforgettable experience for our guests. This isn't just your ordinary little ole BBQ competition where you get 2 to 3 samples.
This is the SPARTA of competitions!
This is a Florida BBQ Association state sanctioned event!
Join us on Friday March 13th and Saturday March 14th and ticketed guests will be able to enter our team competition area  to sample mouth watering BBQ, Chili & Sauces from over 40 of the top BBQ competition teams in the state of Florida and some of our local hometown pitmasters!
Come hungry cause you won't leave that way!
ADVANCE TICKETS
Sample Beers, Wines & Spirits from around the world
Friday and Saturday, enter our beer garden and enjoy samples of aromatic beers and interesting wines from around the world. Choose from over 24 different tastes and discover what you like best.
ADVANCE TICKETS
Rock out to live concerts!
Enjoy the sounds of classic rock to your Irish favorites as we fill the weekend will live bands and artists to give you a Shamrockin' great time!
2 stages with performances late Friday night and all day Saturday and best of all, the concerts are free for you and your friends

BBQ Competition
Florida BBQ Association Backyard Sanctioned Contest
The Charity BBQ & Chili Competition is a fund raiser hosted by the Firefighters Charity Alliance of Central Florida. This fund raiser helps fund our Florian Fund. This fund provides financial assistance to local firefighters enduring catastrophic crisis such as PTSD and cancer treatments. We want this event to be fun for our participants as well as everyone who comes out to attend. The popularity of this event has really grown to be a premier food competition event in Central Florida. We have expanded the event even more this year and have added several fun events as well as community supportive events. We are pleased to announced we are approved as a Florida BBQ Association sanctioned event for Backyard Teams.
Please do not hesitate to contact our organizer with any questions.
​
We look forward to welcoming all these great teams!
